Hi Julia,
During our session today, we covered a lot! We went over some questions on your previous test, and then went over questions on your review for the final. The biggest thing we went over, which you need to remember for the final, is when you have a right triangle with an altitude drawn which creates 3 right triangles. In order to find the missing sides, you can either use the geometric mean or set up proportions with similar triangles. If the hypotenuse of the largest right triangle is not given, you must use proportions. Good luck!
- Brian Sarkozy

4/22/2018
Julia, it was a wonderful to meet you! During our tutoring session, we worked on quite a few problems including area, volume, and converting between units of all three. I really liked how you don't round your answers until the very end - this is something most students do not do! Be sure to determine which shape you are working with first, and try to breakdown compound shapes in all different ways. I am sure you did excellent on your test! I hope to see you again soon. 
- Brian Sarkozy
